    <text>
        <body><div type="bibliography">
                
            <p>Not published before <bibl><ptr target="#IGCyr"/> <citedRange>121600</citedRange></bibl>.</p>
            <p>Cf. <bibl><ptr target="#belzic2022"/>, catalogue <citedRange>B.68</citedRange></bibl>.</p>
            </div><div type="edition" xml:lang="grc" xml:space="preserve">
                
                <ab>
                    <lb n="1"/><persName type="attested" key=""><name nymRef="#Θέαρος">Θέαρος</name> <persName type="attested" key=""><name type="patronymic" nymRef="#Ἑρμήσανδρος">Ἑρμησάνδρ<supplied reason="lost">ω</supplied></name></persName></persName>
	 </ab>
            </div><div type="apparatus" xml:space="preserve">
            
                <p/>
            </div><div type="translation" xml:lang="fr" xml:space="preserve">
            <p>Théaros fils d'Hermésandros.</p>
         </div><div type="translation" xml:lang="en" xml:space="preserve">
            <p>Thearos son of Hermesandros.</p>
            </div><div type="translation" xml:lang="it" xml:space="preserve">
            <p>Thearos figlio di Hermesandros.</p>
         </div><div type="commentary">
                
               <p>This man might be the father of Hermesandros son of Thearos, strategos about 330 BC (<ref type="inscription" source="#IGCyr2">IGCyr017100</ref>), and
              perhaps the grandfather of a son of Thearos, mentionned in <ref type="inscription" source="#IGCyr2">IGCyr014800</ref>, b.18.</p>
	<p/>
	<p/>
            </div></body>
